   415Рєњ## API Reference Рђд
   417Рєњ### `match`
   419Рєњ```ts
   420Рєњmatch(value);
   421Рєњ```
   422Рєњ
   423РєњCreate a `Match` object on which you can later call `.with`, `.when`, `.otherwise` and `.run`.
   424Рєњ
   742Рєњ## Patterns Рђд
   857Рєњ#### `P._` wildcard
   859РєњThe `P._` pattern will match any value. You can also use `P.any`, which is an alias to `P._`.
   860Рєњ
   861Рєњ```ts
   862Рєњimport { match, P } from 'ts-pattern';
   863Рєњ
   864Рєњconst input = 'hello';
   865Рєњ
   866Рєњconst output = match(input)
   867Рєњ  .with(P._, () => 'It will always match')
   868Рєњ  // OR
   869Рєњ  .with(P.any, () => 'It will always match')
   870Рєњ  .otherwise(() => 'This string will never be used');
   871Рєњ
   872Рєњconsole.log(output);
   873Рєњ// => 'It will always match'
   874Рєњ```
   875Рєњ
  1405Рєњ## `P.string` predicates Рђд
  1500Рєњ## `P.number` and `P.bigint` predicates Рђд
  1621Рєњ## Types Рђд
  1623Рєњ### `P.infer`
  1625Рєњ`P.infer<typeof somePattern>` lets you infer a type of value from a type of pattern.
  1626Рєњ
  1627РєњIt's particularly useful when validating an API response.
  1628Рєњ
  1629Рєњ```ts
  1630Рєњconst postPattern = {
  1631Рєњ  title: P.string,
  1632Рєњ  content: P.string,
  1633Рєњ  stars: P.number.between(1, 5).optional(),
  1634Рєњ  author: {
  1635Рєњ    firstName: P.string,
  1636Рєњ    lastName: P.string.optional(),
  1637Рєњ    followerCount: P.number,
  1638Рєњ  },
  1639Рєњ} as const;
  1640Рєњ
  1641Рєњtype Post = P.infer<typeof postPattern>;
  1642Рєњ
  1643Рєњ// posts: Post[]
  1644Рєњconst posts = await fetch(someUrl)
  1645Рєњ  .then((res) => res.json())
  1646Рєњ  .then((res: unknown): Post[] =>
  1647Рєњ    isMatching({ data: P.array(postPattern) }, res) ? res.data : []
  1648Рєњ  );
  1649Рєњ```
  1650Рєњ
      РєњРђд
