docs/v4-to-v5-migration-guide.md
     1Рєњ# TS-Pattern v4 to v5 Migration Guide
     3РєњThis file contains all breaking changes and new features between the version 4 and 5 of TS-Pattern.
     4Рєњ
     5Рєњ# Breaking changes
     7Рєњ## TypeScript v5
     9РєњBecause it relies on [const type parameters](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/release-notes/typescript-5-0.html#const-type-parameters), TS-Pattern v5 requires TypeScript v5+!
    10Рєњ
    11Рєњ## `.with` is now evaluated eagerly Рђд
    42Рєњ## Matching on Map and Sets Рђд
    63Рєњ# New features
    65Рєњ## chainable methods
    67РєњTS-Pattern v5's major addition is the ability to chain methods to narrow down the values matched by primitive patterns, like `P.string` or `P.number`.
    68Рєњ
    69РєњSince a few examples is worth a thousand words, here are a few ways you can use chainable methods:
    70Рєњ
    71Рєњ### P.number methods Рђд
   100Рєњ### P.string methods Рђд
   122Рєњ### Global methods Рђд
   156Рєњ## Variadic tuple patterns Рђд
   214Рєњ## `.returnType` Рђд
